23:00:00","eventDescription":"BROOMFILLER is Toronto, Canada’s answer to melodic punk rock. Blending melodic vocals, bass lines and rhythmic drumming with a very energetic live show, enables them to easily stand out. No strangers to touring, the band toured their sophomore album, “Enter the Storm” twice in the US. (Spring U.S. tour – 41 shows in 46 days & Fall U.S. Tour 54 shows in 60 days), while garnering much praise for their indie DIY work ethic and radio play for their single “The Cause” reaching #1 on Pennsylvania’s college charts. “Enter the Storm” followed on the heels of “Watching the girls go bi”, which received much success and recognition across Canada, USA & Europe. The video for Decide Inside was in rotation on Much Music, and featured on Toronto’s Edge 102. They have toured extensively in Canada since 2002 and in the US since 2004. BROOMFILLER have been compared to Foo Fighters holding hands with Bracket while sitting on a park bench made by Jawboxx & Husker Du, eating a sandwich made by Bad Religion and Face to Face. Enlisting Jordon Zadorozny (Blinker the Star) to produce, their new full length album “Third Stage Propellor Index” was release on August 28th, 2015. The Single “How Long, So Long” has been climbing up the BDS Bullet charts starting from #228 to #128 in one week, as well as hitting the Top 10 (#6) on the 365 Radio Network and Charting #1 on Radio Banks Australia.The Music video had just over 6000 views only 2 months after posting on Facebook. A successful Western Canadian tour in support of the new album was in Sept/Oct. 2015, and will be continued with an Eastern Canadian tour in summer 2016. Request and listen for their 2nd new single Tears Me Apart on radio across Canada and beyond. Be sure to look out for several music videos in support the many singles from the new
